{
  "monitors": [
    {
      "name": "install-extension",
      "model": "openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash",
      "prompt": "You are monitoring a coding agent's output. Look for completion signals — phrases like 'Done', 'this is what we accomplished', 'final set of changes', 'everything should be finished', 'here is a summary of what was done', or similar wrap-up language. ONLY evaluate when these signals appear; if the agent is still mid-work and no completion signal is present, always return triggered: false regardless of content.\n\nWhen a completion signal is present, check if the agent created, wrote, or substantially modified files that look like new pi extensions. A pi extension is: a TypeScript file that exports a default function, likely in .pi/extensions/, ~/.pi/agent/extensions/, or the project root. Look for: registering tools (pi.registerTool), commands (pi.registerCommand), event handlers (pi.on), or custom UI components. Also watch for new agent definition .md files in .pi/agents/ or team definitions in .pi/teams/.\n\nIf the agent created a meaningful new extension, trigger. Do NOT trigger for: minor edits to existing extensions, bug fixes, tweaks, or non-extension code changes.\n\nRespond with ONLY a JSON object: {\"triggered\": true|false, \"reason\": \"what extension was created, or 'no completion signal' or 'no extension work detected'\"}.",
      "message": "A new pi extension may have been created. If so, install it to the user context:\n- Copy .ts extension files to ~/.pi/agent/extensions/\n- Copy agent .md files to ~/.pi/agent/agents/\n- Copy team .md files to ~/.pi/agent/teams/\n\nThen verify with: `find ~/.pi/agent/extensions -name '*.ts' | sort`",
      "minInterval": 2,
      "maxContextTokens": 2000
    },
    {
      "name": "journal-reminder",
      "model": "openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash",
      "prompt": "You are monitoring a coding agent's output. Look for completion signals — phrases like 'Done', 'this is what we accomplished', 'final set of changes', 'everything should be finished', 'here is a summary of what was done', or similar wrap-up language. ONLY evaluate when these signals appear; if no completion signal is present, always return triggered: false regardless of content.\n\nWhen a completion signal is present, check if the agent completed meaningful, non-trivial work that should be documented. Meaningful work includes: building or shipping a feature, fixing a non-trivial bug, making architectural changes, discovering something important, or completing a significant task. Do NOT trigger for: minor typo fixes, trivial one-line changes, answering simple questions, or routine file reads.\n\nRespond with ONLY a JSON object: {\"triggered\": true|false, \"reason\": \"what was accomplished, or 'no completion signal' or 'no meaningful work detected'\"}.",
      "message": "Significant work detected — consider journaling this session in memoriki: append to wiki/log.md and update wiki/index.md if new pages were created. Reason: {reason}",
      "minInterval": 3,
      "maxContextTokens": 2500
    }
  ]
}
